{"title_page": "Wells County, Indiana", "text_new": "{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county          =  Wells County\n| state           = Indiana\n| seal            =\n| founded year    =  1837\n| founded date    =\n| seat wl         =  Bluffton\n| largest city wl = Bluffton\n| area_total_sq_mi = 370.25\n| area_land_sq_mi = 368.09\n| area_water_sq_mi = 2.16\n| area percentage = 0.58%\n| census estimate yr = 2018\n| pop             = 28206\n| density_sq_mi      = 76.6\n| density_km2      = 29\n| time zone       = Eastern\n| footnotes       = Indiana county number 90\n| web             = www.wellscounty.org\n| named for       = [[William Wells (soldier)|William A. Wells]]\n| district = 3rd\n| ex image = Wells County Courthouse P4020318.jpg\n| ex image cap = Wells County Courthouse\n}}\n\n'''Wells County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]].  As of the 2010 census, the population was 27,636.<ref name=\"census-quickfacts\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/18/18179.html\n  |title=Wells County QuickFacts\n  |accessdate=2011-09-25\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>  The [[county seat]] is [[Bluffton, Indiana|Bluffton]].<ref name=\"GR6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx|accessdate=2011-06-07|title=Find a County|publisher=National Association of Counties}}</ref>\n\nWells County is included in the [[Fort Wayne Metropolitan Statistical Area]] and the [[Fort Wayne, Indiana|Fort Wayne]]\u2013[[Huntington, Indiana|Huntington]]\u2013[[Auburn, Indiana|Auburn]] [[Combined Statistical Area]].\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the 2010 census, the county has a total area of {{convert|370.25|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|368.09|sqmi}} (or 99.42%) is land and {{convert|2.16|sqmi}} (or 0.58%) is water.<ref name=\"census-density\"/>\n\n===Adjacent counties===\n* [[Allen County, Indiana|Allen County]]  (north)\n* [[Adams County, Indiana|Adams County]]  (east)\n* [[Jay County, Indiana|Jay County]]  (southeast)\n* [[Blackford County, Indiana|Blackford County]]  (south)\n* [[Grant County, Indiana|Grant County]] (west)\n* [[Huntington County, Indiana|Huntington County]] (northwest)\n\n=== Cities and towns ===\n* [[Bluffton, Indiana|Bluffton]]\n* [[Markle, Indiana|Markle]]\n* [[Ossian, Indiana|Ossian]]\n* [[Poneto, Indiana|Poneto]]\n* [[Uniondale, Indiana|Uniondale]]\n* [[Vera Cruz, Indiana|Vera Cruz]]\n* [[Zanesville, Indiana|Zanesville]]\n\n=== Unincorporated towns ===\n{|\n|----- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* [[Craigville, Indiana|Craigville]]\n* [[Curryville, Indiana|Curryville]]\n* [[Dillman, Indiana|Dillman]]\n* [[Domestic, Indiana|Domestic]]\n* [[Five Points, Wells County, Indiana|Five Points]]\n* [[Greenville, Wells County, Indiana|Greenville]]\n* [[Greenwood, Wells County, Indiana|Greenwood]]\n* [[Jeff, Indiana|Jeff]]\n* [[Keystone, Indiana|Keystone]]\n* [[Kingsland, Indiana|Kingsland]]\n* [[Liberty Center, Indiana|Liberty Center]]\n* [[McNatts, Indiana|McNatts]]\n* [[Mount Zion, Indiana|Mount Zion]]\n|\n* [[Murray, Indiana|Murray]]\n* [[North Oaks, Indiana|North Oaks]]\n* [[Nottingham, Indiana|Nottingham]]\n* [[Petroleum, Indiana|Petroleum]]\n* [[Phenix, Indiana|Phenix]]\n* [[Reiffsburg, Indiana|Reiffsburg]]\n* [[Riverside, Wells County, Indiana|Riverside]]\n* [[Rockford, Wells County, Indiana|Rockford]]\n* [[Tocsin, Indiana|Tocsin]]\n* [[Toll Gate Heights, Indiana|Toll Gate Heights]]\n* [[Travisville, Indiana|Travisville]]\n* [[Wellsburg, Indiana|Wellsburg]]\n|}\n\n===Townships===\n{|\n|----- valign=\"top\"\n|\n* [[Chester Township, Wells County, Indiana|Chester]]\n* [[Harrison Township, Wells County, Indiana|Harrison]]\n* [[Jackson Township, Wells County, Indiana|Jackson]]\n* [[Jefferson Township, Wells County, Indiana|Jefferson]]\n* [[Lancaster Township, Wells County, Indiana|Lancaster]]\n|\n* [[Liberty Township, Wells County, Indiana|Liberty]]\n* [[Nottingham Township, Wells County, Indiana|Nottingham]]\n* [[Rockcreek Township, Wells County, Indiana|Rockcreek]]\n* [[Union Township, Wells County, Indiana|Union]]\n|}\n\n===Major highways===\n* [[File:I-69.svg|20px]] [[Interstate 69 in Indiana|Interstate 69]]\n* [[File:US 224.svg|20px]] [[U.S. Route 224 (Indiana)|U.S. Route 224]]\n* [[File:indiana 1.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 1|State Road 1]]\n* [[File:indiana 3.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 3|State Road 3]]\n* [[File:indiana 116.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 116|State Road 116]]\n* [[File:indiana 124.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 124|State Road 124]]\n* [[File:indiana 201.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 201|State Road 201]]\n* [[File:indiana 218.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 218|State Road 218]]\n* [[File:indiana 301.svg|20px]] [[Indiana State Road 301|State Road 301]]\n\n==History==\nWells County was formed in 1837. It was named for Capt. [[William Wells (soldier)|William A. Wells]], who was captured by [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]] as a young boy and adopted by the [[Miami tribe|Miami]] chief [[Michikinikwa|Little Turtle]]. He eventually became a scout for Gen. [[Anthony Wayne|\"Mad Anthony\" Wayne]]. Capt. Wells was killed by [[Potawatomi]] allied with the British at the [[Battle of Fort Dearborn]] at the outbreak of the [[War of 1812]]. The Potawatomi ate Capt. Wells' heart to gain part of his courage.\n\nThere was also an accident that occurred at the [[clock tower]] of the county courthouse.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} While either fixing or building the roof, a man fell to the grounds of Main Street. He landed on his legs, and he lived for about a week before dying. The force of the fall thrust his [[human pelvis|pelvis]] into his [[rib cage]]. Had he fallen any other way, he would have died on the spot.\n\n== Climate and weather ==\n{{climate chart\n|[[Bluffton, Indiana]]\n|16|30|2.00\n|19|34|1.83\n|29|46|2.58\n|40|58|3.21\n|51|70|4.11\n|61|80|3.92\n|64|84|3.90\n|62|81|3.70\n|55|75|3.07\n|42|63|2.53\n|33|48|3.04\n|23|35|2.65\n|float=right\n|units=imperial\n|clear=both\n|source=The Weather Channel<ref name=\"weather\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://www.weather.com/weather/wxclimatology/monthly/graph/USIN0047\n  |title=Monthly Averages for Bluffton, Indiana\n  |accessdate=2011-01-27\n  |publisher=The Weather Channel\n}}</ref>}}\nIn recent years, average temperatures in Bluffton have ranged from a low of {{convert|16|\u00b0F}} in January to a high of {{convert|84|\u00b0F}} in July, although a record low of {{convert|-24|\u00b0F}} was recorded in January 1985 and a record high of {{convert|104|\u00b0F}} was recorded in July 1980.  Average monthly precipitation ranged from {{convert|1.83|in}} in February to {{convert|4.11|in}} in May.<ref name=\"weather\"/>\n\n==Government==\n{{see also|Government of Indiana}}\nThe county government is a constitutional body, and is granted specific powers by the [[Constitution of Indiana]], and by the [[Indiana Code]].\n\n'''County Council:''' The county council is the legislative branch of the county government and controls all the spending and revenue collection in the county. Representatives are elected from county districts. The council members serve four-year terms. They are responsible for setting salaries, the annual budget, and special spending. The council also has limited authority to impose local taxes, in the form of an income and property tax that is subject to state level approval, excise taxes, and service taxes.<ref name = inc3623>{{cite web|author=[[Indiana Code]]|url=http://www.in.gov/legislative/ic/code/title36/ar2/ch3.html |title=Title 36, Article 2, Section 3|accessdate=2008-09-16|publisher=IN.gov}}</ref><ref name = inc2102>{{cite web|author= [[Indiana Code]] |url= http://www.in.gov/legislative/ic/code/title3/ar10/ch2.pdf |format=PDF|title= Title 2, Article 10, Section 2 |accessdate=2008-09-16|publisher=IN.gov}}</ref>\n\n'''Board of Commissioners:''' The executive body of the county is made of a board of commissioners. The commissioners are elected county-wide, in staggered terms, and each serves a four-year term. One of the commissioners, typically the most senior, serves as president. The commissioners are charged with executing the acts legislated by the council, collecting revenue, and managing the day-to-day functions of the county government.<ref name = inc3623/><ref name = inc2102/>\n\n'''Court:''' The county maintains a [[small claims court]] that can handle some civil cases. The judge on the court is elected to a term of four years and must be a member of the Indiana Bar Association. The judge is assisted by a constable who is also elected to a four-year term. In some cases, court decisions can be appealed to the state level [[circuit court]].<ref name = inc2102/>\n\n'''County Officials:''' The county has several other elected offices, including [[sheriff]], [[coroner]], [[auditor]], [[treasurer]], [[recorder of deeds|recorder]], [[Surveying|surveyor]], and circuit court [[Court clerk|clerk]]. Each of these elected officers serves a term of four years and oversees a different part of county government. Members elected to county government positions are required to declare [[political party|party]] affiliations and to be residents of the county.<ref name = inc2102/>\n\n{{Hidden begin\n|titlestyle = background:#ccccff;\n|title      = Presidential elections results\n}}\n{| align=\"center\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"float:right; margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ '''Presidential elections results'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS|title=Dave Leip's Atlas of U.S. Presidential Elections|last=Leip|first=David|website=uselectionatlas.org|access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref>\n|- bgcolor=lightgrey\n! Year\n! [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n! [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n! [[Third Party (United States)|Third parties]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|