n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1900 United States presidential election|1900]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|37.5% ''2,290''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''58.9%''' ''3,599''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|3.6% ''217''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1896 United States presidential election|1896]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|36.6% ''2,212''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''61.7%''' ''3,728''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|1.6% ''98''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1892 United States presidential election|1892]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|33.9% ''1,668''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''55.4%''' ''2,725''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|10.7% ''528''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''[[1888 United States presidential election|1888]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Republican}}|37.2% ''1,926''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" {{Party shading/Democratic}}|'''56.8%''' ''2,942''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|6.1% ''314''\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1840= 1822\n|1850= 6152\n|1860= 10844\n|1870= 13585\n|1880= 18442\n|1890= 21514\n|1900= 23449\n|1910= 22418\n|1920= 20509\n|1930= 18411\n|1940= 19099\n|1950= 19564\n|1960= 21220\n|1970= 23821\n|1980= 25401\n|1990= 25948\n|2000= 27600\n|2010= 27636\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=28206\n|estref=\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=U.S. Decennial Census|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><br />1790-1960<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu|title=Historical Census Browser|publisher=University of Virginia Library|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref> 1900-1990<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/in190090.txt|title=Population of Counties by Decennial Census: 1900 to 1990|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref><br />1990-2000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|title=Census 2000 PHC-T-4. Ranking Tables for Counties: 1990 and 2000|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 10, 2014}}</ref> 2010-2013<ref name=\"census-quickfacts\"/> 2018<ref name=2018pop>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/wellscountyindiana/PST045218 |title=QuickFacts. Wells County, Indiana. |publisher=United States Census Bureau |accessdate=July 26, 2019 }}</ref>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[2010 United States Census]], there were 27,636&nbsp;people, 10,780&nbsp;households, and 7,684&nbsp;families residing in the county.<ref name=\"census-dp1\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US18179\n  |title=DP-1 Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213020926/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US18179\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The population density was {{convert|75.1|PD/sqmi}}. There were 11,659 housing units at an average density of {{convert|31.7|/sqmi}}.<ref name=\"census-density\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18179\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |title=Population, Housing Units, Area, and Density: 2010 - County\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212204438/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18179\n  |archive-date=2020-02-12\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The racial makeup of the county was 97.3% white, 0.4% Asian, 0.3% American Indian, 0.3% black or African American, 0.8% from other races, and 0.9% from two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin made up 2.0% of the population.<ref name=\"census-dp1\"/> In terms of ancestry, 38.4% were [[Germans|German]], 12.3% were [[English people|English]], 10.8% were [[Irish people|Irish]], and 10.3% were [[Americans|American]].<ref name=\"census-dp2\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0400000US18%7c0500000US18179\n  |title=DP02 SELECTED SOCIAL CHARACTERISTICS IN THE UNITED STATES \u2013 2006-2010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214002503/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0400000US18%7C0500000US18179\n  |archive-date=2020-02-14\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\nOf the 10,780&nbsp;households, 33.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 58.1% were married couples living together, 8.6% had a female householder with no husband present, 28.7% were non-families, and 24.8% of all households were made up of individuals. The average household size was 2.52 and the average family size was 3.00. The median age was 40.2 years.<ref name=\"census-dp1\"/>\n\nThe median income for a household in the county was $47,697 and the median income for a family was $56,885. Males had a median income of $41,871 versus $30,031 for females. The per capita income for the county was $23,169. About 6.2% of families and 8.0% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 10.8% of those under age 18 and 3.6% of those age 65 or over.<ref name=\"census-dp3\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0400000US18%7c0500000US18179\n  |title=DP03 SELECTED ECONOMIC CHARACTERISTICS \u2013 2006-2010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2015-07-10\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200214002931/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0400000US18%7C0500000US18179\n  |archive-date=2020-02-14\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[National Register of Historic Places listings in Wells County, Indiana]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ohiohistorycentral.org/entry.php?rec=403 William Wells]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n<!--added under references heading by script-assisted edit-->\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = Wells County, Indiana\n|North     = [[Allen County, Indiana|Allen County]]\n|Northeast =\n|East      = [[Adams County, Indiana|Adams County]]\n|Southeast = [[Jay County, Indiana|Jay County]]\n|South     = [[Blackford County, Indiana|Blackford County]]\n|Southwest =\n|West      = [[Grant County, Indiana|Grant County]]\n|Northwest = [[Huntington County, Indiana|Huntington County]]\n}}\n{{Wells County, Indiana}}\n{{Fort Wayne Metro}}\n{{Indiana}}\n\n{{coord|40.73|-85.22|display=title|type:adm2nd_region:US-IN_source:UScensus1990}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Wells County, Indiana| ]]\n[[Category:Indiana counties]]\n[[Category:1837 establishments in Indiana]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1837]]\n[[Category:Fort Wayne, IN Metropolitan Statistical Area]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county          =  Wells County\n| state           = Indiana\n| seal            = \n| founded year    =  1837\n| founded date    =\n| seat wl         =  Bluffton\n| largest city wl = Bluffton\n| area_total_sq_mi = 370.25\n| area_land_sq_mi = 368.09\n| area_water_sq_mi = 2.16\n| area percentage = 0.58%\n| census estimate yr = 2018\n| pop             = 28206\n| density_sq_mi      = 76.6\n| density_km2      = 29\n| time zone       = Eastern\n| footnotes       = Indiana county number 90\n| web             = www.wellscounty.org\n| named for       = [[William Wells (soldier)|William A. Wells]]\n| district = 3rd\n| ex image = Wells County Courthouse P4020318.jpg\n| ex image cap = Wells County Courthouse\n}}\n\n'''Wells County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] located in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]].  As of the 2010 census, the population was 27,636.<ref name=\"census-quickfacts\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/18/18179.html\n  |title=Wells County QuickFacts\n  |accessdate=2011-09-25\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>  The [[county seat]] is [[Bluffton, Indiana|Bluffton]].<ref name=\"GR6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx|accessdate=2011-06-07|title=Find a County|publisher=National Association of Counties}}</ref>\n\nWells County is included in the [[Fort Wayne Metropolitan Statistical Area]] and the [[Fort Wayne, Indiana|Fort Wayne]]\u2013[[Huntington, Indiana|Huntington]]\u2013[[Auburn, Indiana|Auburn]] [[Combined Statistical Area]].\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the 2010 census, the county has a total area of {{convert|370.25|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|368.09|sqmi}} (or 99.42%) is land and {{convert|2.16|sqmi}} (or 0.58%) is water.<ref name=\"census-density\"/>\n\n===Adjacent counties===\n*[[Allen County, Indiana|Allen County]]  (north)\n*[[Adams County, Indiana|Adams County]]  (east)\n*[[Jay County, Indiana|Jay County]]  (southeast)\n*[[Blackford County, Indiana|Blackford County]]  (south)\n*[[Grant County, Indiana|Grant County]] (west)\n*[[Huntington County, Indiana|Huntington County]] (northwest)\n\n=== Cities and towns ===\n*[[Bluffton, Indiana|Bluffton]]\n*[[Markle, Indiana|Markle]]\n*[[Ossian, Indiana|Ossian]]\n*[[Poneto, Indiana|Poneto]]\n*[[Uniondale, Indiana|Uniondale]]\n*[[Vera Cruz, Indiana|Vera Cruz]]\n*[[Zanesville, Indiana|Zanesville]]\n\n=== Unincorporated towns ===\n{|\n|----- valign=\"top\"\n|\n